% Write `pdd/commands/contracts.py`.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Requirements
- Implement `@click.group(name="contracts")` with a `check` subcommand.
- `contracts check TARGET` accepts file or directory, plus optional `--stories` directory.
- Support `--json` output and `--strict` warning escalation.
- Exit codes: 0 clean, 1 warnings, 2 errors or strict warnings.
- Use `pdd.contract_check` public API for evaluation.
- Wire `--review off|explain` (default `off`) using the `review_option` decorator from `pdd.commands.checkup_review_options`.
- Compute the deterministic exit code before any LLM call; the advisory pass MUST NOT alter the exit code.
- When `--review explain` is set: call the advisory LLM pass per result; on any exception set `advisory.status="failed"` and continue; inject `"advisory": report_as_dict(report)` as a sibling key per item in the JSON array (parallel to the existing `"waivers"` key); in non-JSON mode print a brief advisory summary to stderr.
- When `--review off` (default): no LLM calls; JSON output is unchanged.
- Import `SKIPPED_REPORT`, `failed_report`, `final_exit_code`, `report_as_dict` from `pdd.checkup_advisory`.

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/commands/contracts.py`
